2002 Pirelli Tower plane crash is an aviation disaster that occurred on 8 March 2002 on the Italian island of Isola del Giglio when a Germanwings A320 crashed into the mountain after being struck by lightning and then burst into flames, killing all 150 people onboard. The plane was destined for Barcelona, Spain, but the last communication with controllers was received at 01:44 GMT. The airline stated, however, that its own radar detected two objects which were presumed to be objects from the downed airplane.
